Januas cuts down on setup time, gives you a fresh contemporary interface, allows you to embed event ticketing codes and works well on mobile, which is really the point if you are running an event</p>\n\t\t\t    </div>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t<!-- happy-slide__text-wrap -->\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- happy-slide__text-wrapp -->\n\t\t\t<li class=\"happy-slide__text-wrap \" data-index=\"6\">\n\t\t\t    <div>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Event Manager Theme lets my clients concentrate on planning events because it was created with event planners in mind. Built on the Genesis framework, easy to update, secure, and stunningly beautiful, these WordPress themes are top notch and my first choice for events of any size. </p>\n\t\t\t    </div>\n\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t<!-- happy-slide__text-wrap -->\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- happy-slide__text-wrapp -->\n\t\t\t<li class=\"happy-slide__text-wrap \" data-index=\"7\">\n\t\t\t    <div>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Event Manager Theme theme is very hip, very now.
